text: IFK Strängnäs is a sports club in the town of Strängnäs in Sweden. It was established in 1899. The club runs track and field athletics, handball, disabled sports, orienteering. Earlier the club also played bandy. The men's bandy team played in the Swedish top division in 1931. and 1932. == References == ==Other websites== *Official website Category:1899 establishments in Sweden Category:Bandy clubs in Sweden Category:Handball clubs in Sweden
